I would like to be able to customize the default behavior of the "Quick Search" field.
If I type in "one two", without the " it results in the following search:
{noformat}
summary ~ "one two" OR description ~ "one two" OR comment ~ "one two"
{noformat}
I would like the search to perform:
{noformat}
summary ~ "+one +two" OR description ~ "+one +two" OR comment ~ "+one +two"
{noformat}
as I would type "+one +two" in quick search.

My users are complaining, that any modern search solution would search this way "one&&two", if given two terms, where Jira searches "one||two" which multiplies the number of results and makes it useless.

Can this be achieved easily?

